# TESS Program G07077

Title: Planetary Systems Around Thick-Disk Stars

PI: Dai, Fei - University Of Hawaii (Manoa)

Type: SMALL

Summary: TESS has successfully achieved its Level-1 Requirement to determine the masses of at least 50 sub-Neptunes. However, only a few of those are around thick-disk stars. The iron-depleted but alpha-enhanced chemistry of thick-disk stars may naturally favor the formation of planets with smaller iron core but larger silicate mantles. The ~10-Gyr-old planets also show us the mature stage of both geological and ecological evolution. Thanks to Gaia and ground-based medium-resolution spectroscopic surveys, we can now propose a targeted survey of thick-disk planet hosts to offset their underrepresentation in the solar neighborhood. We propose transit search of 10k thick-disk candidate stars, and ground-based radial velocity measurements of 8 thick-disk rocky planets.
